<html><head></head><body><div style="font-family: Verdana;font-size: 12.0px;"><div>The School of Natural Sciences at the University of California, Merced invites applications for<br/>
one tenure-track Assistant Professor position in the areas of Statistics, Probability, and Stochastic<br/>
Processes. The position will be in the Applied Mathematics Unit at UC Merced.</div>

<div class="signature">
<div>Special attention will be paid to applicants who participate in interdisciplinary research, applicants<br/>
who will contribute to developing the statistics curriculum, and applicants who will contribute<br/>
to one or more of the campus research initiatives in the natural sciences, engineering and/or<br/>
social sciences.</div>

<div>Qualifications: Successful candidates should have a Ph.D. in Statistics, Applied Mathematics,<br/>
or related field. We seek a candidate with post-doctoral experience in Statistics, Applied Mathematics,<br/>
or related field.</div>

<div>Deadline: October 31, 2016. Review of applications will begin on November 1, 2016.</div>

<div>Applications must be submitted via https://aprecruit.ucmerced.edu/apply/JPF00390.</div>

<div>Applications must include (1) a cover letter stating area of interest, (2) curriculum vitae (3)<br/>
teaching statement, (4) diversity statement, and (5) four letters of recommendation, among which<br/>
one must address teaching, submitted directly prior to the application deadline. After an application<br/>
is submitted, the letters of reference should be electronically uploaded by the letter writers<br/>
(instructions will be provided by the application system).</div>

<div>The University of California, Merced opened in September 2005 as the tenth campus of the<br/>
University of California and the first American research university built in the 21st century. In<br/>
keeping with the mission of the University to provide teaching, research and public service of the<br/>
highest quality, UC Merced will be providing new educational opportunities at the undergraduate,<br/>
masters and doctoral levels through three academic schools: Engineering, Natural Sciences and<br/>
Social Sciences, Humanities and the Arts. The University of California, Merced is an affirmative<br/>
action/equal opportunity employer with a strong institutional commitment to the achievement of<br/>
diversity among its faculty, staff, and students. The University is supportive of dual career couples.<br/>
Salary is commensurate with education, experience, and UC academic salary scales.</div>

<div>Questions are most welcome! Please contact the chair of the search committee, Prof. Harish<br/>
S. Bhat, at hbhat@ucmerced.edu.</div>
